            Bio
            I develop data analytics applications in support of bioscience research. My primary focus is on developing graph databases that integrate data from multiple scientific and clinical repositories. Current projects include a graph database that supports data related to ALS and a statistical analysis of synonymous mutations in cancer. My personal interests include cycling, music, and reading history. My favorite place on Earth is The Rose Main Reading Room in NYC.
            
            
            Education
            The Johns Hopkins University | Baltimore, MD
            M.S. in Bioinformatics
            The New Jersey Institute of Technology | Newark, NJ
            B.S. in Engineering Science
            
            
            Experience
            BioGraphDb | Bioinformatics Consultant | 2019 - Present
            New York Genome Center | Senior Software Engineer, Bioinformatics | 2015 - 2018
            Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center | Bioinformatics Software Engineer | 2014 - 2015
